## Context

A common topic of developers is the chair we sit on. Well what chair do I use?

[![reddit]](https://old.reddit.com/r/webdev/comments/tyuehk/web_devs_what_chairs_do_you_use/)

The popular choice is not always the best choice. The Ikea Markus shows a lot on those discussions. Ikea creates cheap, easy to find, good enough product.
It is understandable to see this one so much.

![markus]

In fact I own one and I still use it from time to time like on this open table about [gamification](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=06HIy-8L_gM):

[![alois+markus]](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=06HIy-8L_gM)

But this is more a "chilling chair" than a work chair. My main one is not a chair, it is a stool.

## Ergonomic Stool

Note that an ergonomic stool is also known as a kneeling chair.

![my stool]

### Why?

Science currently mostly says that they are best for my health. I like my health so why not?

- These results suggest that, compared to a conventional chair, the use of a kneeling chair enables a more efficient upright sitting posture with lower trunk muscle activity, as well as a more efficient slump sitting posture with a smaller reduction in lordosis of the lumbar spine: [Comparison of Trunk Muscle Activities and Spinal Curvature when Sitting on a Kneeling Chair and Sitting on a Conventional Chair -- Investigation of Two Sitting Postures.](https://web.p.ebscohost.com/abstract?direct=true&profile=ehost&scope=site&authtype=crawler&jrnl=13411667&AN=65480485&h=SsGPdee6wUJELIi09mbHmcZHGd916bA%2bMYrPuo3Y0wkZEJZg7z9OOx7wSvhTSoNtDcuJLgWlrcORaVNbxHWRHg%3d%3d&crl=c&resultNs=AdminWebAuth&resultLocal=ErrCrlNotAuth&crlhashurl=login.aspx%3fdirect%3dtrue%26profile%3dehost%26scope%3dsite%26authtype%3dcrawler%26jrnl%3d13411667%26AN%3d65480485)
- This study suggests that ergonomically designed kneeling chairs set at +20deg inclination do maintain standing lumbar curvature to a greater extent than sitting on a standard computer chair with an overall mean difference of 7.633: [Ergonomically designed kneeling chairs are they worth it?](https://books.google.fr/books?hl=fr&lr=&id=htZCkFTqDe0C&oi=fnd&pg=PA103&dq=Kneeling+Chair&ots=6P7QCv_Vnj&sig=ZY2GP-JFDnuCED2PmedyFYT3w_M&redir_esc=y#v=onepage&q=Kneeling%20Chair&f=false)
- The kneeling chair results in the lowest hip joint reaction force and hip flexion: [Computer-based estimation of the hip joint reaction force and hip flexion angle in three different sitting configurations](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/abs/pii/S0003687017300947)
- Balans Chair (semi kneeling): [The Balans chair and its semi-kneeling position: an ergonomic comparison with the conventional sitting position.](https://europepmc.org/article/med/2954222)
- [Palliative Interventions for Sedentary Low Back Pain: The Physiotherapy Ball, the Kneeling Chair and Conventional Ergonomics Compared](https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/abs/10.1177/154193120004402923)
- [Effect of a kneeling chair on lumbar curvature in patients with low back pain and healthy controls: A pilot study](https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S1877065715000445)

### Which?

You can find a lot of different model online. I do not really know which one I use. I don't because I got mine for free online.

They can be quite cheap. 20€ second-handed or around 100€ new.

![lbc1]

and if you don't like it, put it back online. I won't judge.
